  "prompt": "Can a person who is blind from birth dream?",
  "response": "Yes, a person who is blind from birth can and does dream. Their dreams may not include visual imagery, as they have never had visual experiences, but they can experience dreams involving other senses such as sound, touch, taste, and smell. Many blind individuals report that their dreams are rich in auditory and tactile sensations, and they can also incorporate emotional and conceptual experiences. The nature of dreaming can vary significantly from person to person, but the ability to dream is not dependent on sight.",
